				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">goldsong's rant page<a name="38080"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 4 04 11:42 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok don't know if any of you have had the same questions come us like I have as too who is the best puller.  bard monk and ranger.  well i got to find out the fun way.  we had all three in one group and every one of them thought they were the ultimate puller.  now I love my bard tune.  however we are just no compotition to monks.  It eventually happens someone resists a song or we dont see a mob around a corner that is fine so we get an add then we mezz or what ever we have to do.  but having feign death (especially as a hotkey) is the only way to go.  we pull very well in the absence of a monk.  but we already have a job.  no one goes on raids with out at least one bard.  they cant.  resistant checks any more go at 300.  majority of people cannot get there with out help from us.  lets not take the job of other classes also.  aside from being the best meele's in the game the only job a monk has is to pull.  THAT IS WHY THEY ARE BETTER.  yeah they can deliver alot of damage,  but no where near a ranger with true shot or a rogue with the new discs.  SO LET THEM PULL!  our job is haste resist and slow.  or what ever the job calls for.  </span></td>
