				<td colspan="2"><span>I pull better than about 75% of the monks I know.  I have outstanding tools for the job, as do they, but there is some degree of technique involved here and some of them just don't have it.  I am quick to admit that there are monks out there that pull better than I do and I quickly yeild to them once they demonstrate that fact.  Frankly, for my guild, the combination of Mookane da Monk at point and me at his slack to tag or support him is the best pulling team I have ever seen in action, thank you very much!
<br />

<br />
But the other day in Sol Ro tower, we were in the Protector's tower and got to those demon guys -- you know where there are two of them across the hall from each other, each one surrounded by 3 mephits making for about 8 mobs with overlapping agro ranges and two of them big nasty level 68s --- and I brought out one of those bad boys with a single mephit that was easy mez bait.  And I am a pretty average bard.
<br />

<br />
So in answer to your rant, I will gladly let a monk do the pulling if he is better at it than I am.  But many of them aren't and those guys need to step aside and let someone else do the job.  They're as bad as the arrogant bards who never pulled before in their lives but figure since they're a bard, it has to be easy, right?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
