				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Seperate adventure groups<a name="38091"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 4 04 12:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>They should make 3 different adventure's
<br />
     1.  for the players trying to get armor proc's and the numerous great things that can come of adventures.
<br />

<br />
     2.  for the true newbies and ebayers that seem to infest adventure groups like a bad case of diarea.  almost nothing makes me more aggrovated then when I get a tell in poV trying to find a group and i get &quot;want an adv?&quot;  so i make the run while asking him you got a full group already or do i need to look for others?  he say's nope we are all full just waiting on you.  I get there head over to zone in and the group is 3 rangers a rogue a monk and myself.  WTF.  thanks for wasting my run time.
<br />

<br />
     3.  for window licking, blue koolaid drinking, paintchip eating, short buss riders.  these are different then newbies because they can fool you in first glance.  They somehow get to 65 and look like they know what they are doing.  this would be the shadowknight that cannot hold taunt off of the ranger or the bard.  the cleric that is oom after one kill.  the shaman that cannot keep buffs up. the chanter that tashes at 99 percent then yells when they die 8 times.  (and yells at everyone but the tank) etc.  
<br />

<br />
so my solution is you would be able to weed these things out if it was &quot;want an iav&quot;  &quot;want an adv&quot; and &quot;want an eadv&quot;  then all the ebayers could play together.  the windowlickers could all sit around and look at female dark elf's all day.  and the rest of us would be able to enjoy a normal adventure where no one dies and it only takes 30 min.</span></td>
