				<td colspan="2"><span>65 Bard and 65 Monk here...
<br />

<br />
I have pulled a variety of mobs on both toons.  I simply have more tools to draw from as a Bard than I will ever have as a Monk.  I can single pull with both, but I can do it far faster with my Bard than my monk.  In addition, I can single pull a mob and have 1, 2, 3, etc planned adds trickle into camp on my timeline not the mobs.
<br />

<br />
Our raids our pulled mostly by monks.  They are superb at what they do.  But I would suggest that pulling mobs to a large raid force ready to kick a$ is different than single group crawling in a place like Sol Ro or Earth or LDoN.  The disparity between a bard and a monk in those arenas becomes more obvious.
<br />

<br />
I do agree with you that the job that a monks skills are most suited for is pulling.  But this disparity between what a monk can do fullfilling this role and what a bard can bring to that role and so many others is sadly why I dont play my monk anymore.
