				<td colspan="2"><span>Personally I find Lyrisa's post depressing and entirely too negative.  Apparently in your guild or on your servers monks either totally suck or they quit the game.  I'm sorry to hear that.  We have a monk in our guild who pulls better than any monk or bard I have ever known.  There is a monk in our allied guild who is almost as good.  No, they don't automatically split every single pull unless I have TOLD them to do that for some insane reason.  On trash mobs, I usually go with either two or three MAs and make sure the monks have a mob on each at all times.  One of the few exceptions is with the Gindan mobs in Tactics that split.  I err on the side of caution and have my pullers bring those single, not that it takes any time or talent to get singles in Tactics.  I OFTEN use a single monk puller on large scale raids, but they never single pull.  The two concepts are not glued together at all.
<br />

<br />
What bugs me about this discussion is all the absolutes.  Monks are not absolutely better pullers than bards.  Bards are not absolutely better pullers than monks. Monks are not an inherently flawed and useless class.  These statements are ignorant and wildly inaccurate and they display a profound lack of understanding or experience with the two classes.  My guild which has only 50 main characters, has 6 level 65 paladins.  I've been told this is a total waste of manpower and I should order people to re-roll some characters and PL them back up which is just an asinine statement.  I chose a different path.  I re-write the 'conventional' strats to take advantage of the skills and classes and playing styles of my guild.  I delight in the fact that I can have paladin group heals going off in every single group.  I am delighted that I have more off-tanks than you can shake a stick at.  I love the fact that I can use an LOH chain to live through half the tough bosses in POP that we fight, if I get the insane urge to do that.  There is no useless class in this game and the simple fact is, monks do some very useful things pulling that we can't do and vice versa.</span></td>
