				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: how come there is no evil raced bards<a name="38480"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 5 04 9:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We're in the rant n rave section =) don't take my post to seriously, I was definitely defending the position from an extremists point of view. 
<br />
Monks... i love them, but I think their getting jipped big time and its not the bards or monks or necro's that are doing it, its just an imbalance that has occured that needs to be corrected. 
<br />
I love to pull.. I love to pull as part of a team, I prefer teams made up of a variety of classes with multiple pulling skills and techniques. This is my true feelings on the matter. When I pull for a group its more like I choreograph the beginning movements of the group than pull, marking targets.. mt assisting and targeting, chanters or shammy's prepared for casters and melee debuffs on targets.. preparing the group for a charge or movement. 
<br />
I pulled an Ary raid this afternoon in Solro where it was more a matter of preparing tanks for their targets and peeling minimum amounts of  mobs out of large bunches than pulls persay. Having a monk to work with that could have moved large groups of mobs to obsolete edges while I peeled others away would have been immensely helpful and I mourn the passing of so many great pullers who played monks and were burnt out by the restrictions of the class. 
<br />
